                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2772: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-26T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1922—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. Your 172, October 17, 2 p.m. and Department’s 73, July 17, 3 p.m.<note
                        n="12" xml:id="d763fn12">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_920">pp. 920</ref> and <ref
                            target="#pg_907">907</ref>, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Advise Foreign Office Italian Government has just expressed its concurrence in
                    original proposal also that French Government concurs in proposal to wind up
                    international control October 31.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
